<h1 class="hero-h">2026 AI tool cost reference <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for B2B buyers.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">A comprehensive May 2026 pricing reference for the AI tools mid-market B2B companies actually evaluate — Claude, ChatGPT, Microsoft Copilot, Google Gemini, GitHub Copilot, Cursor — with tier-by-tier comparison, what each tier includes, and what real organizations spend. Designed to be cited; updated quarterly.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">About this reference</span><h2 class="h2">Methodology and citation rules</h2><p class="body"><strong>Purpose:</strong> A single citable reference for AI tool pricing in B2B settings as of May 2026. Built for journalists, analysts, and buyers who need to anchor cost claims with reliable numbers.</p><p class="body"><strong>Sources:</strong> Public vendor pricing pages, Treetop's negotiated rates across ~60 mid-market engagements, peer firms and operator conversations, and competitor pricing visibility through May 2026.</p><div class="callout"><p><strong>Permission to cite:</strong> Yes. Attribution: "Treetop Growth Strategy, 2026 AI Tool Cost Reference, May 2026 — treetopgrowthstrategy.com/ai-tool-cost-reference-2026". This URL is stable; we update quarterly. Last refresh: May 2026.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Claude (Anthropic)</span><h2 class="h2">Tiers and pricing</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>Price</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Free</strong></td><td>\$0</td><td>Personal exploration; never business data</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pro</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month</td><td>Individual heavy users; non-confidential business work</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Team</strong></td><td>\$30/user/month (min 5 seats)</td><td>B2B teams 5-150; most mid-market default</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Enterprise</strong></td><td>Custom (typically \$60-\$100/user/month effective)</td><td>150+ seats; regulated industries; SSO/SCIM/BAA needed</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3 class="h3">API pricing (Claude Sonnet 4.7, May 2026)</h3><ul class="ul"><li>Input tokens: ~\$3 per million tokens</li><li>Output tokens: ~\$15 per million tokens</li><li>Typical business prompt: ~\$0.01-\$0.05 per call depending on length</li><li>Prompt caching available — meaningful cost reduction for repeated context</li></ul><p class="body"><strong>Hidden costs:</strong> implementation time, training time, internal admin (8-12 hrs/week of an AI lead during rollout). Often 2-3x the license cost in true Year-1 spend.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">ChatGPT (OpenAI)</span><h2 class="h2">Tiers and pricing</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>Price</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Free</strong></td><td>\$0</td><td>Personal exploration; limited model access</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Plus</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month</td><td>Individual users; some business use</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Team</strong></td><td>\$25-\$30/user/month (min 2 seats)</td><td>B2B teams; most mid-market default for OpenAI ecosystem</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Enterprise</strong></td><td>Custom (typically \$60-\$100/user/month effective)</td><td>Larger orgs; SSO/SCIM/expanded admin</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3 class="h3">API pricing (GPT-5 class, May 2026)</h3><ul class="ul"><li>Pricing has shifted multiple times in 2025-2026; check OpenAI directly</li><li>Roughly comparable to Claude API at the same capability tier</li><li>Vision and audio modalities priced separately</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Microsoft Copilot</span><h2 class="h2">Tiers and pricing</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Product</th><th>Price</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Microsoft 365 Copilot</strong></td><td>\$30/user/month (on top of M365 license)</td><td>Microsoft-heavy stacks; Office integration</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Copilot Pro (consumer)</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month</td><td>Individual Microsoft users</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Copilot Studio</strong></td><td>Custom (capacity-based)</td><td>Custom agent building on Microsoft stack</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GitHub Copilot Business</strong></td><td>\$19/user/month</td><td>Engineering teams on GitHub</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GitHub Copilot Enterprise</strong></td><td>\$39/user/month</td><td>Larger engineering orgs</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p class="body"><strong>Bundling note:</strong> Microsoft 365 Copilot requires existing M365 license — true incremental cost is \$30/user/month on top of M365's own cost (\$10-\$30/user/month depending on tier). Total all-in for a new Microsoft customer can hit \$50-\$60/user/month.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Google Gemini for Workspace</span><h2 class="h2">Tiers and pricing</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>Price</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Gemini Business</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month (on top of Workspace)</td><td>Google Workspace customers</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gemini Enterprise</strong></td><td>\$30/user/month (on top of Workspace)</td><td>Larger Workspace customers needing advanced features</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gemini for Cloud / Code Assist</strong></td><td>\$19-\$45/user/month</td><td>Engineering teams on GCP</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gemini Advanced (consumer)</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month</td><td>Individuals</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p class="body"><strong>Bundling note:</strong> Like Copilot, Gemini requires existing Workspace license. True incremental cost varies.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Specialized coding tools</span><h2 class="h2">Cursor, Windsurf, Claude Code</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Price</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Cursor Pro</strong></td><td>\$20/user/month</td><td>IDE-based AI coding</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cursor Business</strong></td><td>\$40/user/month</td><td>Team admin + privacy mode</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Claude Code</strong></td><td>Included with Claude Pro/Team/Enterprise + API costs</td><td>Terminal-based AI agent</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Windsurf Pro</strong></td><td>\$15/user/month</td><td>IDE-based agent workflows</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GitHub Copilot (above)</strong></td><td>\$19-\$39/user/month</td><td>IDE inline + chat</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Total cost of ownership by company size</span><h2 class="h2">What real organizations actually spend</h2><p class="body">Below is observational data on Year-1 all-in AI tooling spend (platform license + implementation + training + internal admin time) across Treetop's mid-market engagement sample, May 2026:</p><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Company size</th><th>Median Year-1 all-in</th><th>25th-75th percentile</th><th>License % of total</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>10-25 people</td><td>\$11,000</td><td>\$5K-\$22K</td><td>~30%</td></tr><tr><td>25-50 people</td><td>\$28,000</td><td>\$15K-\$55K</td><td>~25%</td></tr><tr><td>50-100 people</td><td>\$68,000</td><td>\$35K-\$130K</td><td>~22%</td></tr><tr><td>100-250 people</td><td>\$185,000</td><td>\$95K-\$320K</td><td>~20%</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="callout"><p><strong>The under-budgeted line item:</strong> internal time (AI lead hours + training time across the team) typically accounts for 40-55% of true Year-1 cost. License costs are typically 15-30% of total. External implementation when used is 15-30%.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Common pricing pitfalls</span><h2 class="h2">Where buyers get surprised</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Bundled platform pricing.</strong> Microsoft and Google require their respective base licenses. True incremental cost is the AI feature on top, not the bundled headline.</li><li><strong>Per-seat vs per-user-active.</strong> Most enterprise tiers charge per-seat regardless of usage. Audit utilization quarterly to right-size.</li><li><strong>Enterprise pricing variance.</strong> Enterprise tiers often have negotiable pricing — published rates are starting points. Bigger commitments unlock 20-40% discounts.</li><li><strong>API + UI double-pay.</strong> If you build custom workflows on the API AND give users UI access, you pay both. Decide architecture before purchasing.</li><li><strong>Context window upgrades.</strong> Some tiers charge separately for extended context (e.g., Claude 1M context). Factor in if your workflows need it.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Pricing trends through 2026</span><h2 class="h2">Where pricing is going</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Per-seat pricing has plateaued</strong> at the \$25-\$40 range for mid-tier business plans. Race-to-the-bottom unlikely; capability differentiation drives premium tiers.</li><li><strong>API pricing has dropped 30-50% across providers</strong> over the last 12 months at equivalent capability tiers — but capability has also expanded.</li><li><strong>Enterprise tiers are becoming more flexible</strong>. SSO, audit, BAA features are increasingly available at the Team tier, narrowing the rationale to upgrade for many mid-market companies.</li><li><strong>Specialized 'AI features' from vertical SaaS vendors are converging on \$10-\$30/user/month</strong>. The 'AI tax' on existing tools is now baked in.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Methodology</span><h2 class="h2">How we put this together</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Vendor pricing pages reviewed May 12-15, 2026.</li><li>Mid-market engagement data: ~60 B2B companies $5M-$50M ARR, Q4 2024-Q2 2026.</li><li>Peer firm conversations: ~15 fractional consultancies and operator interviews.</li><li>Negotiated enterprise rates anonymized and aggregated.</li><li>Pricing changes between refresh cycles noted in change log (when material).</li><li>Refresh cadence: quarterly. Next: August 2026.</li></ul><div class="callout"><p><strong>Permission to cite (again):</strong> Yes, with attribution to Treetop Growth Strategy. Link to this URL — it's the stable canonical reference.</p></div></div></section>

